This paper deals with optimization problems related to caching and paging, which are classic topics in computer science. The use of the k-server problem as a framework for studying these problems suggests that the paper belongs to the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The analysis of competitiveness and the use of game-theoretic concepts suggest that the paper may also belong to the category of game theory (cs.GT). The use of techniques from approximation algorithms and online algorithms suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of algorithms (cs.AL) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the use of probabilistic arguments and the study of worst-case and average-case performance suggest that the paper may also belong to the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
